离汉通道关闭的前一天|图片报道。
Photo coverage the day before Han Channels closed.
作者：王迎春 来源：中国经营网。
Authors: Wang Yingchun Source: China Management Network.
本报记者王迎春 武汉报道1月22日，武汉首次披露肺炎疫情后第23天，湖北省、武汉市两级政府自21日起集中发布关于疫情防护工作动态，特别是在习近平主席做出指示、李克强总理于针对疫情召开国务院常务会议后。
Our correspondent Wang Yingchun Wuhan reported on January 22, 23 days after Wuhan first disclosed the outbreak of pneumonia, the governments of Hubei Province and Wuhan have since 21 concentrated on the epidemic prevention work, especially after President Xi Jinping gave instructions and Premier Li Keqiang convened a State Council executive meeting to address the epidemic.
1月23日清晨，武汉新型冠状病毒感染的肺炎疫情防控指挥部发布1号通告，自23日10时起，武汉停运全城公交、地铁、轮渡、长途客车，市民无特殊原因不离开武汉，机场、火车站离汉通道暂时关闭。
On January 23, Wuhan, the new coronavirus infection of the pneumonia command issued a notice No. 1, from 10: 00, Wuhan stopped the city's public transport, subway, ferry, long-distance bus, without special reasons, the citizens did not leave Wuhan, the airport and railway stations from Han corridor temporarily closed.
于是，1月22日，成为启动上述措施之前的最后一天。
Thus, 22 January was the last day before the above-mentioned measures were initiated.
记者从多个渠道了解到，湖北省、武汉市两级政府近两天以来的相关指示已迅速传递到乡村单位级政府系统。
Reporters learned from many sources, Hubei, Wuhan city government in the past two days the relevant instructions have been quickly transmitted to the system of government at the rural unit level.
另外，全国多个单位已针对疫情向单位员工发布防护工作指导。
In addition, a number of units across the country for the epidemic situation to the unit staff issued protection guidance.
武汉地铁集团已于22日晚间7点40分通过官方微信平台披露，自23日起武汉地铁启动进站体温检测。
Wuhan Metro Group has been 22 night 7: 40 through the official micro-letter platform disclosed that Wuhan Metro from 23 to start the temperature test station.
1月22日，武汉市政府通过官网向市民发布公开信：通过公开信，武汉市政府向市民提示防控措施：出门戴口罩，不要不习惯；勤洗手，不要嫌麻烦；常通风，不要不当回事；不随地吐痰，不乱扔乱倒；少去人多的地方，没有要紧的事不离开武汉；不信谣，不传谣；如果感觉不适，要及时去医院就诊等。
By an open letter, the Wuhan municipal government reminded the public to take preventive and control measures: go out wearing masks, do not be unaccustomed; wash your hands frequently, don't be fussy; not spit everywhere, do not throw things out of Wuhan; fewer people, do not leave Wuhan; do not believe, do not spread rumors; if feel uncomfortable, to go to the hospital in time.
与此同时，湖北省政府于1月22日凌晨宣布启动公共卫生Ⅱ级应急响应，并发布相关通告：此种状况下，记者走访武汉各大超市、市场，发现不少市民仍在外出购物采办年货。
Meanwhile, in the early morning hours of January 22, the Hubei provincial government announced the launch of public health level II emergency response, and issued a notice to this effect: Under the circumstances, reporters visited major supermarkets and markets in Wuhan and found that many citizens were still shopping for New Year's Eve.
图1：菜市场依然热闹，市民忙着备年货，商贩仍在做生意不过商贩王先生对记者介绍，生意这两天已明显不好，人们甚至因为肺炎疫情不敢前来买活鸡。
Photo 1: The Halles market is still busy, citizens are busy preparing the new year goods, traders are still doing business. But Mr. Wang, a vendor, told reporters that business has been noticeably bad these two days and people are afraid to come to buy live chickens because of pneumonia.
王先生原本趁过年多贩卖些土鸡。
Mr. Wang used to sell more turkeys during the New Year.
从各大药店口罩销售情况看，市民戴口罩的意识在加强。
From the major drugstore mask sales, people wearing masks awareness in the strengthening.
一位在武汉长期居住的袁女士对记者介绍，已采购200个口罩。
Ms. Yuan, a longtime resident of Wuhan, told reporters that she had purchased 200 masks.
相比于那些居住在武汉的人们，外地路过武汉、或回武汉探亲的人们显然更加紧张。
Compared with those who live in Wuhan, people who pass by Wuhan or return to Wuhan are obviously more nervous.
生长于武汉，定居于深圳的胡女士于1月18日回武汉，了解到疫情进展后，果断决定不过年三十了，买了1月23日回深圳的返程票。
Ms. Hu, who grew up in Wuhan and settled in Shenzhen, returned to Wuhan on January 18 and, learning of the progress of the epidemic, decided to buy a return ticket to Shenzhen on January 23, only 30 years old.
生长于湖北宜昌定居于苏州的洪女士于1月21日回宜昌，她对记者介绍正在后悔中。
Ms. Hong, who grew up in Suzhou, Yichang, Hubei province, returned to Yichang on January 21 and told reporters that she was regretting.
喻女士此前已订好初三回武汉的机票，21日在得知疫情进展后，决定退票，“探亲重要，但两个孩子的生命安全更重要”她对本报记者介绍。
"Family visit is important, but the lives of the two children are more important," she told the reporter.
另外，一些单位对于有员工回武汉过年的，也显得紧张。
In addition, some units for the staff back to Wuhan New Year, but also appears nervous.
郭先生于1月21日回武汉，当天他就接到领导电话提醒，向人力资源部报备。
Mr. Guo returned to Wuhan on January 21, and on the same day he received a call from his leader to report back to the Ministry of Human Resources.
在深圳某银行工作的邵女士对记者介绍，单位已经发了口罩，并严格统计春节期间去湖北的人员，要求非特殊情况，不要去武汉，如果春节期间去了武汉的同事，也要求延后几天再上班。
Shao, who works for a bank in Shenzhen, told reporters that his unit had already put out masks and strictly counted the people who went to Hubei during the Spring Festival.
值得注意的是，因为湖北省已启动突发公共卫生事件Ⅱ级应急响应，武汉卫健委宣布自22日起不再发布全市肺炎疫情动态，由湖北省卫生健康部门发布。
It is noteworthy that, as a result of the public health emergency response in Hubei Province, the Wuhan Fitness Commission announced that it would no longer publish the city-wide pneumonia epidemic situation from 22 days, which was issued by the Hubei Provincial Health Administration.
1月22日，记者通过多个票务平台查询发现，哪怕22日当天从北京、广州等热点地方前往武汉，仍有余票。
On January 22, through a number of ticket platform inquiries, found that even 22 days from Beijing, Guangzhou and other hot spots to Wuhan, there are still more than tickets.
（编辑：郝成）。
(Editor: Hao Cheng)
